  "description": "Frame encode/decode conformance vectors for protocol version 1. A conformant codec must decode each wire_hex to the described message and re-encode that message to exactly wire_hex. wire_hex is the lowercase hex of the full frame: a 4-byte big-endian body length, a 4-byte big-endian message-type discriminant, then the XDR body. The message field documents the frame for a human and a cross-language implementation; the byte-exact contract is wire_hex. This file covers the handshake, exec, and oplog frames frozen alongside the exec and oplog capabilities; the pre-existing content and management frames are exercised by the in-crate round-trip tests and are appended here as the protocol crate gains serialisable message representations. For the oplog frames the envelope (peer id, sequence, length-prefixed opaque entries) is frozen; the internal byte shape of an entry, its signature, and the deterministic reduce/merge are deliberately not frozen and are the oplog co-design items, so the vector entries carry arbitrary opaque bytes.",
